CVE-2010-1256.summary: Unspecified vulnerability in Microsoft IIS 6.0, 7.0, and 7.5, when Extended Protection for Authentication is enabled, allows remote authenticated users to execute arbitrary code via unknown vectors related to "token checking" that trigger memory corruption, aka "IIS Authentication Memory Corruption Vulnerability."

CVE-2010-2730.summary: Buffer overflow in Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) 7.5, when FastCGI is enabled, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via crafted headers in a request, aka "Request Header Buffer Overflow Vulnerability."

CVE-2010-3972.summary: Heap-based buffer overflow in the TELNET_STREAM_CONTEXT::OnSendData function in ftpsvc.dll in Microsoft FTP Service 7.0 and 7.5 for Internet Information Services (IIS) 7.0, and IIS 7.5, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (daemon crash) via a crafted FTP command, aka "IIS FTP Service Heap Buffer Overrun Vulnerability." NOTE: some of these details are obtained from third party information.

CVE-2010-1899.summary: Stack consumption vulnerability in the ASP implementation in Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) 5.1, 6.0, 7.0, and 7.5 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (daemon outage) via a crafted request, related to asp.dll, aka "IIS Repeated Parameter Request Denial of Service Vulnerability."

CVE-2012-2531.summary: Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) 7.5 uses weak permissions for the Operational log, which allows local users to discover credentials by reading this file, aka "Password Disclosure Vulnerability."

Quality Agility Equipment : Highest Quality Professional A-Frames and Dog Walks for Competitive Arena : Canvasworks Inc. : Kennebunk, Maine : Steve Eberle

If you have looked at the rest, you need to look at the best! Introducing Quality Agility Contact Equipment designed and fabricated by agility devotees to provide the best A Frames and Dog Walks for training your canines.

  • Fabricated of 1/8" extremely high grade sheet aluminum custom welded to our exacting specifications.

  • Meets all specific requirements for competition associations.

  • No long waits for your equipment to arrive.

  • As about our "White Glove Customer Service." You may qualify for free delivery and set up, thus saving expensive shipping and handling.

  • Equipment comes complete with a proprietary formula high tech rubber chip surface providing traction and security.

  • Beginner to champion, this contact equipment will be the only contact equipment you'll ever need to buy.


Click each thumbnail image for enlarged detail.



"The Jesse"
Dog Walk
   Everything you look for in a Dog Walk ~ stability, no torque, no bounce. Canines gain confidence on our high tech rubber surface and well defined contact areas. Quality Agility Equipment utilizes a unique one hinge system to attach the plank to the one and off ramps and rolling leg system. This system enables the unit to fold and be stored in a relatively flat space. Quality Agility Equipment meets all regulations at a height of 48" and our exclusive hinged leg system can be dropped to 24" in a matter of seconds to get the beginning canine started. We use only the best rolling and locking rubber caster system for ease in moving and rapid resetting of trial courses.



"The Wellington"
A Frame

   A wonderful training tool, our A Frame has the same high tech quality construction as the Dog Walk. Designed to be easily adjustable for beginner to advanced high energy canines. The A Frame comes standard with our blue and yellow specially designed rubber chip surface, with our unique single hinge design system. We have eliminated the dangerous gap that exists in most A Frames and contact equipment on the market. An option offered with the A Frame system is a foldable and/or removable wheel frame system for ease of movement on various surfaces including grass. Included are wide casters of dense rubber.
